Date: Thu, 9 Jul 2026 11:40:56 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 2/4] VideoPlayer: tonemap HDR thumbnails via swscale color
 management

Replace the legacy pointer conversion in ExtractThumbToTexture with
sws_scale_frame on color-tagged AVFrames. libswscale 9 performs
gamut mapping and PQ/HLG tone mapping from the frame tags and the
mastering-display metadata, so HDR thumbnails become proper SDR
instead of washed-out gray, and SDR BT.2020 content gains correct
gamut mapping. The legacy path remains as compile-time fallback for
older system FFmpeg and as runtime fallback when sws_scale_frame
rejects a conversion. A failed conversion now returns no texture
instead of uninitialized pixels.
